be really proud of yourself.

26:05.563 --> 26:06.982
{\an3}You should look at where you
were, you know, six months ago.

26:07.065 --> 26:08.650
{\an1}- And I--no, and I am
proud of myself, yeah...

26:08.733 --> 26:10.485
{\an3}- And then where you are now,
you know what I mean?

26:10.568 --> 26:12.946
{\an1}- No, I'm definitely proud
of myself, but I'm not 100% yet.

26:13.029 --> 26:15.156
- It's admirable.

26:15.240 --> 26:16.491
{\an1}- Thanks.

26:18.076 --> 26:20.287
- Hmm.
- What?

26:20.370 --> 26:22.789
{\an3}- I can't believe we haven't
seen Carly in a year.

26:22.872 --> 26:24.332
We need to figure something out.

26:24.416 --> 26:26.501
- Yeah.
- I'm pretty sure Dawn--

26:26.584 --> 26:27.669
{\an1}- Might know a little bit
more than we do?

26:27.752 --> 26:30.880
Maybe, you know, like--

26:30.964 --> 26:32.674
{\an3}- Well, maybe we can talk
to Dawn about it.

26:32.757 --> 26:34.509
{\an3}What do you feel, though,
about the visit, like?

26:34.592 --> 26:36.219
- Hopefully sometime, you know,

26:36.303 --> 26:38.179
it doesn't have to be right
this year like I told you,

26:38.263 --> 26:39.681
{\an1}but hopefully for spring break,
we can try to get together,

26:39.764 --> 26:41.683
or Christmas break or something.

26:41.766 --> 26:43.184
{\an1}We'll see.

26:43.268 --> 26:44.853
{\an1}I mean, I guess I'm just glad
that with the show

26:44.936 --> 26:46.855
that we can still talk
about Carly and, like,

26:46.938 --> 26:49.024
{\an1}our feelings or, you know,
stuff like that.

26:49.107 --> 26:53.403
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:53.486 --> 26:55.322
{\an3}- We got pretty lucky,
though, didn't we?

26:55.405 --> 26:56.448
- I think so, honey.

26:56.531 --> 26:57.866
- We got to marry
our best friend.

26:57.949 --> 26:59.200
- I know, how cool is that?

26:59.284 --> 27:00.577
{\an1}Not a lot of people
get to do that.

27:00.660 --> 27:01.703
{\an3}- No.

27:01.786 --> 27:03.163
{\an3}I love you.

27:03.246 --> 27:07.709
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:07.792 --> 27:10.045
{\an8}<i>- I have a lot to do before</i>
<i>my furniture store opens,</i>

27:10.128 --> 27:11.880
{\an8}<i>so I hope while my mom</i>
<i>is visiting</i>

27:11.963 --> 27:13.506
{\an8}<i>she stays out of the way.</i>

27:13.590 --> 27:15.383
{\an7}Super excited, I'm happy
you're doing the job.

27:15.467 --> 27:17.260
{\an8}Doing the job, thank you.

27:17.344 --> 27:24.309
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:25.643 --> 27:27.645
{\an8}[doorbell dings]

27:27.729 --> 27:29.522
{\an7}Oh, my God. Grandma doesn't even
know how to get in the door.

27:29.606 --> 27:31.775
{\an8}Hello.
- Hey.

27:31.858 --> 27:34.444
{\an8}- Good to see you.
- I think you look gorgeous.

27:34.527 --> 27:36.404
{\an8}- Oh, thanks.
- It's good to see you.

27:36.488 --> 27:38.031
{\an8}- Hi, how are you?
- How are you?

27:38.114 --> 27:39.574
{\an8}Where's my Sophia?
- Grandma's here.

27:39.657 --> 27:41.368
{\an9}Sophia's doing
science projects.

27:41.451 --> 27:42.369
{\an7}- Science?

27:42.452 --> 27:43.828
{\an8}- [exclaiming]

27:43.912 --> 27:45.622
{\an8}- Well, I missed you guys.

27:45.705 --> 27:47.749
{\an3}- Mom, good for that
you're back.

27:47.832 --> 27:49.417
{\an3}People [bleep] normally
go visit their families...

27:49.501 --> 27:50.877
{\an1}- I'm just telling you,
it's been busy.

27:50.960 --> 27:52.545
{\an3}- It doesn't--
it's not a big deal.

27:52.629 --> 27:54.339
Yeah, it's been busy.
- It's been so busy.

27:54.422 --> 27:56.758
{\an3}- Life is great.
Let's just keep it moving.

27:56.841 --> 28:00.929
{\an1}- I got a surprise for your mama
that I thought would be great

28:01.012 --> 28:04.057
{\an1}because she's opening up
a new store, you know?

28:04.140 --> 28:06.101
Just give me one second.

28:06.184 --> 28:08.645
